72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:28): Depending on exactly what was in the proto area at the time, probably not.
72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:28): it'll have the same effect BFU does, but with less safety in the process.  The checksums in the package DB will no longer be correct.
6c728b2ae6e0bdb14ac212ed5f74c1d8 (01:28): richlowe: only stuff for /lib and /usr/bin, no kernel parts
72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:28): if the stuff in the proto area wasn't packaged in the first place, "maybe"
6c728b2ae6e0bdb14ac212ed5f74c1d8 (01:30): richlowe: I hope "tar" is clever enougth to unlink inodes before writing over them.
72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:31): I'd still heartily recommend using the tools that exist to do such things.
72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:31): and wherever tar put the files, if they're packaged, and they're different, the checksum in the DB will no longer be the same.
6c728b2ae6e0bdb14ac212ed5f74c1d8 (01:31): richlowe: the tools won't work as there is no package stuff for libshell&co.
72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:31): nrubsig: well, you're going to need package stuff, sounds like a good point to do it :)
6c728b2ae6e0bdb14ac212ed5f74c1d8 (01:32): that is currently not really a problem. getting reviews seems to be a problem... ;-(
72bac19ca0a2ff15f99326a8f7e02c10 (01:33): while I'm no expert on such things, I'd expect the package stuff to be part of what was reviewed, too.
